9 Relating to Etowah County; to amend Section 45-28-243,
10 Code of Alabama 1975; to increase the amount of time necessary
11 for accommodations supplied to be exempt from privilege and
12 license tax in the county.
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
14 Section 1. Section 45-28-243 of the Code of Alabama
15 1975, is amended to read as follows:
16 "§45-28-243
17 (a) In Etowah County, there is hereby levied and
18 imposed, in addition to all other taxes of every kind now
19 imposed by law, a privilege or license tax upon every person,
20 firm, or corporation engaging in the business of renting or
21 furnishing any room or rooms, lodging, or accommodations to
22 transients in any hotel, motel, inn, tourist camp, tourist
23 cabin, or any other place in which rooms, lodgings, or
24 accommodations are regularly furnished to transients for a
25 consideration, in an amount of two percent of the charge for
26 such room, rooms, lodgings, or accommodations, including the
27 charge for use or rental of personal property and services
28 furnished in such the room. There is exempted from the tax
Page 1

furnished in such the room. There is exempted from the tax
HB632 INTRODUCED
29 levied under this section any taxes on rentals or services
30 under Division 1, commencing with Section 40-23-1, of Article
31 1, Chapter 23, Title 40. The tax shall not apply to rooms,
32 lodgings, or accommodations supplied for a period of 30 180
33 continuous days or more in any place.
34 (b) Municipal privilege license taxes which are levied
35 and collected by the application of a flat percentage rate on
36 gross sales or gross receipts from sales, and which are passed
37 on directly by the licensee-seller to the purchaser-consumer
38 or user shall be excluded from gross sales or gross receipts,
39 as the case may be, in the computation of the tax herein
40 levied in this section.
41 (c) The tax herein levied in this section shall be
42 collected in the same manner as the state lodgings tax as
43 provided in Chapter 26, Title 40, and shall be additional
44 thereto; and the net proceeds thereof of the tax shall be
45 payable to the county general fund for the purposes on of
46 promoting tourism and beautification. Such The funds shall be
47 used as follows: Fifty percent for the support and promotion
48 of tourism and fifty 50 percent for the support and promotion
49 of beautification and ecology as determined by the resolutions
50 of the Clean and Beautiful Community Commission and the
51 Gadsden-Etowah County Tourism Board. The State Department of
52 Revenue shall promulgate such adopt rules and regulations and
53 provide such forms and instructions as are necessary to
54 implement this section."
55 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
56 1, 2026.
